NEW YORK (AP) — Two people died in a fire that tore through three small residential buildings in Queens on Friday.The New York City fire department reported the deaths occurred as the homes were destroyed by a fire in the South Ozone Park neighborhood. Two other buildings were damaged by the afternoon fire.Authorities said the bodies were recovered from a basement. The identities of the dead were not immediately released.More than 50 fire units responded to the blaze. An investigation was underway to determine the fire’s cause.